docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 12. -- The marked effect of the Spanish civil war on United States trade with that nation was shown today by figures made public by the Department of Commerce. Total exports from this country to Spain in September were valued at only $245,000, compared with $3,734,000 in September last year.
